5. Create database
To create a new database execute the following command.
use DATABASE_NAME. use is command and database_name is your databse.


6. Know your current selected database
> db
Mydb
>
db represent the current database where we are working.


7. Create collection
To create the new collection execute the following commands
Syntax: db.createCollection(name)

> use Firstdb
switched to db Firstdb
> db.createCollection("Employee")
{ "ok" : 1 }
>


8. To check collections list
To get the list of collections created execute the following command
Syntax: show collections

> show collections
Employee
>


10. Drop collection
To drop the selected collection execute the following command
Syntax: db.COLLECTION_NAME.drop()

> db.Employee.drop()
true
>
